        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 24 at 7:12PM CDT until April 24 at 8:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Cimarron County in the Panhandle of Oklahoma...

* Until 815 PM CDT.

* At 711 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles northeast
of Felt, or 14 miles southwest of Boise City, moving east at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

* Locations impacted include...
Felt and Boise City.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
